Using the spread operator `...` with `String.fromCharCode` on a `Uint8Array` can throw a `RangeError: Maximum call stack size exceeded` if the course data is large (e.g., a course with many holes or long names/descriptions). It is safer and more robust to use a standard loop to build the binary string before encoding it to base64.

```typescript
export function encodeCourseShare(course: Course): string {
	const json = JSON.stringify(course);
	const bytes = new TextEncoder().encode(json);
	let binary = "";
	for (let i = 0; i < bytes.length; i++) {
		binary += String.fromCharCode(bytes[i]);
	}
	const base64 = btoa(binary);
	return base64.replaceAll("+", "-").replaceAll("/", "_").replace(/=+$/, "");
}
```

