When `startLocationTracking` is called multiple times (for example, when clicking the 'Try Again' button in the error overlay), the previous `watchId` is overwritten without being cleared. This leaks active geolocation watches in the background, draining the device's battery and causing redundant state updates. Clearing the existing watch before starting a new one prevents this leak.

```
const startLocationTracking = () => {
	if (watchId !== null) {
		navigator.geolocation.clearWatch(watchId);
		watchId = null;
	}
	if (!navigator.geolocation) {
		locationError =
			"Geolocation is not supported by this browser. You can still explore in demo mode.";
		isLoading = false;
		return;
	}
```

![medium](https://www.gstatic.com/codereviewagent/medium-priority.svg)

The standard `atob` function can throw a `DOMException` if the base64 string is not correctly padded (since the padding `=` characters were stripped during encoding). Restoring the padding before decoding ensures compatibility across all standard environments.

```suggestion
export function decodeCourseShare(code: string): Course | null {
	try {
		const base64 = code.replaceAll("-", "+").replaceAll("_", "/");
		const padded = base64.padEnd(base64.length + (4 - (base64.length % 4)) % 4, "=");
		const bytes = Uint8Array.from(atob(padded), (ch) => ch.charCodeAt(0));
		const parsed: unknown = JSON.parse(new TextDecoder().decode(bytes));
		if (!isValidCourse(parsed)) {
			return null;
		}
		// Re-key imported courses so they never collide with existing ids
		return { ...parsed, id: generateId(), builtIn: false };
	} catch {
		return null;
	}
}
```

