Completed or abandoned game sessions are left in `localStorage` under `discgolf.game.[id]` indefinitely, which can eventually exceed the browser's 5MB storage quota. Cleaning up the previous game session when starting a new one prevents this storage accumulation.

```suggestion
export function createGame(course: Course): GameSession {
	const previousId = getCurrentGameId();
	if (previousId) {
		removeKey(GAME_KEY_PREFIX + previousId);
	}
	const session: GameSession = {
		id: generateId(),
		course,
		currentHoleIndex: 0,
		strokes: course.holes.map(() => 0),
		startedAt: Date.now(),
		completedAt: null,
	};
	saveGame(session);
	writeJson(CURRENT_GAME_KEY, session.id);
	return session;
}
```

![medium](https://www.gstatic.com/codereviewagent/medium-priority.svg)

If `onVisibilityChange` is triggered when the page is already visible and a wake lock is already active, calling `request()` again will overwrite the `sentinel` reference with a new one. This leaks the old active sentinel, making it impossible to manually release it later. Checking if the sentinel is already active or released before requesting a new one prevents this leak.

```suggestion
	const onVisibilityChange = () => {
		if (!released && document.visibilityState === "visible" && (!sentinel || sentinel.released)) {
			request();
		}
	};
```

